metatags.og:description: For the first-time flyer, air travel can seem like a daunting task. Where do you buy a ticket? What happens when you get to the airport? Do you need identification? Although the options and questions seem endless, there is no need to worry: as long as you can read and ask questions, you can successfully fly. To make your first flight less stressful, it is helpful to have an idea of what to expect.
